article.description: Briann January scored a career-best 25 points, tying a school record with seven 3-pointers in No. 25 Arizona State's 73-59 victory over UC Davis on Wednesday night.
article.headline: January scores 25, including school-record seven 3-pointers, in ASU win
article.linkText: January pushes No. 25 Arizona State by UC Davis
article.story:
DAVIS, Calif. -- Briann January scored a career-best 25 points, tying a school record with seven 3-pointers in No. 25 Arizona State's 73-59 victory over UC Davis on Wednesday night.

Dymond Simon added 20 points for the Sun Devils (4-2), who set another school record with 14 3-pointers against the Aggies (3-2), including 7-of-9 shooting by January, the Pac-10's defensive player of the year last season. Arizona State's previous record was 10 3-pointers against Stanford on Jan. 21, 2006.

Paige Mintun scored 18 points to lead UC Davis (3-2), which fell behind by 15 points in the first half of a rare visit to The Pavilion from a ranked team.
